# bhcom-ba (Angular 21)

Logistics/admin SPA. Prefer existing abstractions over new UI frameworks.

## Commands

- `npm start` — dev server (4200)
- `npm run build` / `npm test` — build / Vitest

## Source map (read files when implementing, don’t guess)

- Routes: `src/app/app.routes.ts`
- App shell: `src/app/layout/` — `app-shell`, `sidebar`, `topbar`
- Sidebar nav: `src/app/layout/sidebar/sidebar-nav.config.ts` (keep in sync with routes)
- Layout services: `src/app/core/layout/sidebar.service.ts` (desktop collapse + mobile drawer), `theme/`, `i18n/`
- Forms framework: `src/app/core/form/` — export barrel `index.ts`
- Tables framework: `src/app/core/table/` — export barrel `index.ts`
- Features: `src/app/features/<domain>/`
- i18n: `public/assets/en.json` + `bh.json` (add keys to both)
- Theme + layout tokens: `src/styles.scss` (`--bg-*`, `--text-*`, `--layout-padding-*`, form/table vars)
- Breakpoints: `src/styles/_breakpoints.scss` (`@mixin below-md`), `src/app/core/layout/viewport.ts` (`MOBILE_BREAKPOINT_PX` = 768)

## Layout behavior (do not reimplement ad hoc)

- **Desktop:** persistent sidebar (`SidebarService.collapsed`), panel collapse/expand in sidebar brand row.
- **Mobile (≤768px):** topbar hamburger → `SidebarService.openMobile()`; drawer overlay + backdrop in `app-shell`; X closes drawer; nav scrolls inside sidebar; auto-close on route change / Escape / backdrop.
- **Main scroll:** `.app-shell__content` only — sidebar is viewport-height with internal nav scroll.

## References for patterns

- Simple form page: `features/fleet/vehicles/create-vehicle-page.*` + `create-vehicle.form.ts`
- Stepper + custom sections: `features/shipments/create-shipment/`
- List/table page: `features/shipments/shipments-page.*` + `shipment.table.ts`
